Pollution in the US

Kamil Simka
2014/12/31

Presentation Description

The goal of this presentation is to describe the Shiny application, created as a final project of Developing Data Products in the Data Science specialization track.

Pollution in the US

The purpose of my application is to allow users to check pollution scale for a specific location in the United States of America.

Datasets for this application has been made available by the United States Environmental Protection Agency (EPA), and can be downloaded here:

annual_all_2014.zip,

annual_all_2013.zip.

The application can be accessed at the following URL: https://kksimka.shinyapps.io/Pollution_in_the_US/

Pollution in the US cities

pollutant2013 and pollutant2014 functions can be used to calculate levels of PM2.5 for a specific latitude and longitude.

The barplot on the left compares PM2.5 levels in different US cities.

Pollution in the US cities

Nevertheless, it is often uncomfortable to insert various values, when someone wants to evaluate pollution levels for multiple locations.
